SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
This is a hard-negative confusor where professional de-escalation succeeds:
  1. Agitated arrival — client is already upset; presents their issue loudly.
  2. Escalation attempt — client raises voice, makes accusations.
  3. Worker validation — worker acknowledges the client's frustration empathically.
  4. Problem-solving offer — worker identifies something concrete they CAN do.
  5. Client calms — frustration reduces; the session ends with partial resolution.
